And that song changed a
lot for me, which is crazy.

00:14:59.500 --> 00:15:01.250
I've done this for a lot
of years, like I mentioned.

00:15:01.250 --> 00:15:02.650
I've played in a lot of bands.

00:15:02.650 --> 00:15:06.290
And I sort of wrote
this song as, like,

00:15:06.290 --> 00:15:11.765
a introduction of myself
to my soon-to-be baby girl.

00:15:11.765 --> 00:15:13.640
And interestingly enough,
for a lot of people

00:15:13.640 --> 00:15:16.490
it became the introduction to
me as an artist altogether.

00:15:16.490 --> 00:15:18.020
Because it was
really the first song

00:15:18.020 --> 00:15:21.330
I ever had that got
substantial radio play

00:15:21.330 --> 00:15:23.300
and a lot of exposure on.

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:27.440
So she's a good luck charm
for more reasons than one.

00:15:27.440 --> 00:15:31.870
And she turned five last
week, which is crazy to me.

00:15:31.870 --> 00:15:35.337
But yeah, so this one is called
"Cecilia and The Satellite."

